ausibility evidence comes from studies using techniques such as in situ hybridization and immunohistochemistry to identify Ahr and Ahr-related gene and protein expression in lower jaw structures of a variety of animals. For example, Ahr mRNA and protein are present in mouse craniofacial tissue (Abbott et al. 1994a; Abbott et al. 1998), Ahr and Arnt protein are expressed in human embryonic palatal cells (Abbott et al. 1994b), and Ahr2 and cyp1a are expressed in the craniofacial region (including the Meckel&rsquo;s cartilage) of zebrafish (Mattingly et al. 2001; Teraoka et al. 2002).", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:47:48 +0000 2026"}